race.comment: LADY MILAN (11) debuts for the premier stable and owns three sharp Doomben trials and race rider Ben Thompson sticks from them. Jumps from an inside barrier and on what we've seen she'll take beating. DAITANNA (2) resumes and has placed 2/2 fresh. She's threatened to win in decent Maidens and her lead-up trials have been good. Maloney is flying and is a key jockey engagement. ZANJEER (1) resumes and has switched from James Cummings. He led well-supported at Newcastle on debut but folded up at the business end. He was nudged out in a recent Doomben trial with Huxtable on and he sticks. Maps well and the lsate betting will be key. WAYBURN (8) debuts for Matt Dunn and owns a Gold Coast trial win. Mallyon stays with him and he has to be kept onside.
